column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The essence of life, each additional Gold Ankh gives extra health capacity.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The essence of life, each additional Gold Ankh gives extra health capacity.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Die Essenz des Lebens. Jedes weitere Goldankh erhöht den Gesundheitsvorrat.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>L'essence de la vie - chaque Ankh d'or augmente ton capital-santé.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Es la esencia de vida: cada Ankh de oro adicional aumenta el nivel de salud.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Ogni Ankh d'oro è l'essenza della vita e fornisce una riserva aggiuntiva di salute.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>생명에너지로 바뀐 황금 앙크는 체력을 올려준다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>命の本質、ゴールドアンクを集めれば集めるほど体力の限界が増える。<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The essence of life, each additional Gold Ankh gives extra health capacity.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column15: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The essence of life, each additional Gold Ankh gives extra health capacity.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A essência da vida: cada Ankh de Ouro adicional aumenta sua capacidade de saúde.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>4 Gold Ankh Pieces can be reformed into an extra Gold Ankh by a person with the right skills.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>4 Gold Ankh Pieces can be reformed into an extra Gold Ankh by a person with the right skills.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>4 Goldankh-Teile können von einer Person mit entsprechenden Fähigkeiten zu einem Goldankh zusammengesetzt werden.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>4 Bouts d'Ankh d'or peuvent être liés pour former un Ankh d'or par une personne compétente.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Alguien con habilidades adecuadas puede convertir 4 trozos de Ankh de oro en un Ankh de oro.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>4 pezzi di Ankh d'oro, uniti da una persona con le giuste abilità, possono formare un'Ankh d'oro.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>4개의 황금 앙크 조각들은 어떤 능력을 가진 사람에 의해 다른 황금 앙크로 변형될 수 있다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>特別な技術を知っている人は4つのゴールドアンクのかけらを１つのゴールドアンクにまとめることができる。<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>4 Gold Ankh Pieces can be reformed into an extra Gold Ankh by a person with the right skills.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column15: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>4 Gold Ankh Pieces can be reformed into an extra Gold Ankh by a person with the right skills.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>4 pedaços de Ankh de Ouro podem ser convertidos em um Ankh de Ouro completo por alguém com as habilidades certas.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A sacred vase which contains a fragment of Tutankhamen's soul.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A sacred vase which contains a fragment of Tutankhamen's soul.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Ein heiliges Gefäß, das einen Teil von Tutankhamens Seele enthält.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Vase sacré contenant un peu de l'âme de Toutankhamon.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Vasija sagrada que contiene una parte del alma de Tutankamón.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Un vaso sacro che contiene un frammento dell'anima di Tutankhamon.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>신성한 화병으로 투탕카멘의 영혼의 조각을 담고 있다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>ツタンカーメンの魂のかけらを持つ聖なるな壼。<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A sacred vase which contains a fragment of Tutankhamen's soul.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column15: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A sacred vase which contains a fragment of Tutankhamen's soul.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Um vaso sagrado que contém um fragmento da alma de Tutancâmon.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A blue diamond that belongs to the Corridor of Champions game master. Return it to him to prove your worthiness for the wall gauntlets.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>

column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Bringe ihn zu ihm, um zu beweisen, dass du der Herausforderung gewachsen bist.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Diamant bleu appartenant au maître du jeu Corridor des Champions. Rapporte-le lui pour lui prouver que tu peux relever le défi.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Diamante azul perteneciente al Maestro de la prueba Pasaje de los Campeones. Devuélveselo para demostrarle que mereces afrontar el reto.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Un diamante che appartiene al gestore della Galleria dei Campioni. Riportaglielo per dimostrare che meriti di affrontare la sfida.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>푸른 다이아몬드로써 승자 회랑의 게임 마스터의 소유이다. 이것을 그에게 돌려주어 벽의 시련에서의 너의 가치를 입증하라.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>廊下のチャンピオンのゲームマスターの青いダイヤモンド。ウォールガントレットにふさわしいことを証明するためにゲームマスターに返す。<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A blue diamond that belongs to the Corridor of Champions game master. Return it to him to prove your worthiness for the wall gauntlets.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>

column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Um diamante azul que pertence ao mestre do Corredor dos Campeões. Devolva-o para provar que é digno do desafio das paredes.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>This tome contains incantations to send Bas-Ket to Uruk Castle with Canopic Vases for the Mummy.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>This tome contains incantations to send Bas-Ket to Uruk Castle with Canopic Vases for the Mummy.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Dieser Wälzer enthält die Beschwörungen, um Tragek-Orb mit einer Urne für die Mumie zum Palast von Uruk zu entsenden.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Ce livre d'incantations peut envoyer Khorb-Èye au Palais d'Uruk avec des Vases canopes pour la Momie.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Libro que contiene indicaciones para enviar a Kan-Asta al Palacio de Uruk con Canopes para la Momia.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Questo tomo contiene magie capaci di inviare Bas-Ket al Castello di Uruk con i Vasi canopi per la Mummia.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>이 책은 바스-켓과 미이라를 위한 납골단지들을 우루크 성으로 함께 보낼 수 있는 주문을 담고 있다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>この魔術書はマミーにカノポス壺を届けるためにバス・ケットをウルク城まで移送できる呪文を持っている。<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>This tome contains incantations to send Bas-Ket to Uruk Castle with Canopic Vases for the Mummy.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Livro que contém encantamentos para enviar Ces-To ao Castelo de Uruk com Vasos Canópicos para a Múmia.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Beetles which can be used to capture monsters.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Beetles which can be used to capture monsters.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Käfer, die zum Fangen von Monstern benutzt werden können.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Insectes permettant de capturer des monstres.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Escarabajos que se usan para capturar monstruos.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Coleotteri usati per catturare mostri.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>괴물들을 포획하기 위해 사용되는 딱정벌레들.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>モンスターを捕まえるために使用できるビートル。<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Beetles which can be used to capture monsters.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>These darts magically regenerate giving you an infinite supply. They are only powerful enough to damage explosive monsters.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>These darts magically regenerate giving you an infinite supply. They are only powerful enough to damage explosive monsters.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Der Vorrat dieser magischen Pfeile erneuert sich immer wieder. Mit ihnen können lediglich explosive Monster verletzt werden.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Ces flèches se régénèrent à l'infini. Elles ne peuvent endommager que les monstres explosifs.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Dardos que se regeneran mágicamente y nunca se agotan. Tan solo tienen fuerza para dañar a monstruos explosivos.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Questi dardi si rigenerano magicamente, dandoti una riserva infinita. Riescono a danneggiare solo i mostri esplosivi.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>다트들은 마법으로 무제한 생겨난다. 그러나 폭발성의 괴물들에게는 작은 상처만 줄 수 있을뿐이다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>このダーツは魔法で補充するので供給は無限だ。爆発型モンスターにしかダメージを与えることができない。<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>These darts magically regenerate giving you an infinite supply. They are only powerful enough to damage explosive monsters.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column15: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>These darts magically regenerate giving you an infinite supply. They are only powerful enough to damage explosive monsters.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Estes dardos se regeneram magicamente, criando um estoque infinito. Possuem força suficiente apenas para ferir monstros explosivos.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>These darts magically regenerate giving you an infinite supply. They bounce off surfaces to hit targets indirectly but are only powerful enough to damage explosive monsters.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>These darts magically regenerate giving you an infinite supply. They bounce off surfaces to hit targets indirectly but are only powerful enough to damage explosive monsters.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Der Vorrat dieser magischen Pfeile erneuert sich immer wieder. Sie prallen von Wänden ab und treffen ihr Ziel indirekt. Mit ihnen können lediglich explosive Monster verletzt werden.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Ces flèches se régénèrent à l'infini. Elles rebondissent plusieurs fois avant de toucher la cible. Elles ne peuvent endommager que les monstres explosifs.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Dardos que se regeneran mágicamente y nunca se agotan. Rebotan en superficies para golpear objetivos de forma indirecta. Tan solo tienen fuerza para herir monstruos explosivos.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Questi dardi si rigenerano magicamente, dandoti una riserva infinita. Rimbalzano sulle superfici per colpire in modo indiretto ma riescono a danneggiare solo i mostri esplosivi.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>다트들은 마법으로 무제한 생겨난다. 이것은 과녁들을 멀리서도 맞출 수 있지만, 폭발성의 괴물들에게는 작은 상처를 줄 수 있을뿐이다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd><ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>このダーツは魔法で補充するので供給は無限だ。目標を間接的に打つために表面から跳ね返ることができる、けど爆発型モンスターにしかダメージを与えることができない。<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>These darts magically regenerate giving you an infinite supply. They bounce off surfaces to hit targets indirectly but are only powerful enough to damage explosive monsters.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column15: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>These darts magically regenerate giving you an infinite supply. They bounce off surfaces to hit targets indirectly but are only powerful enough to damage explosive monsters.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Estes dardos se regeneram magicamente, criando um estoque infinito. Eles rebatem superfícies para acertar alvos indiretamente, mas possuem força suficiente apenas para ferir monstros explosivos.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6:
These warriors for the Geb Queen are gargantuan in size and vicious with it...

Good luck to anyone who faces one of these in combat.
column7:
These warriors for the Geb Queen are gargantuan in size and vicious with it...

Good luck to anyone who faces one of these in combat.
column8:
Diese Krieger der Gebkönigin sind gigantisch und sehr gefährlich...

Viel Glück, wenn du deinem solchen begegnest.
column9:
Les guerriers de la Reine des Gebs sont aussi imposants que méchants...

Bonne chance à ceux qui auront à les combattre!
column10:
Guerreros de la Reina Geb de tamaño titánico y muy sanguinarios.

Buena suerte a quien se enfrente a ellos en combate.
column11:
Questi guerrieri della regina Geb sono feroci e anche colossali...

Buona fortuna a chiunque ne debba affrontare uno in combattimento.
column12:
이 겝 여왕의 용사들은 엄청나게 잔인하다...

전투에서 이들을 대면하는 자들에게 행운이 있기를.
column13:
このゲブクイーンの巨大な戦士は悪質…

このモンスターと戦う者へ武運を。
column14:
These warriors for the Geb Queen are gargantuan in size and vicious with it...

Good luck to anyone who faces one of these in combat.
column15:
These warriors for the Geb Queen are gargantuan in size and vicious with it...

Good luck to anyone who faces one of these in combat.
column16:
Estes guerreiros da Rainha Geb têm um tamanho imenso e são crueis...

Boa sorte a qualquer um que encare um destes em combate.

column6:
An eccentric member of the Burble species which uses its horns to attack...

Their cloth hats have been worn for so many generations, they now grow atop their heads from birth.
column7:
An eccentric member of the Burble species which uses its horns to attack...

Their cloth hats have been worn for so many generations, they now grow atop their heads from birth.
column8:
Eine exzentrische Art der Fettsackfamilie. Benutzt die Hörner zum Angreifen...

Hüte tragen sie schon seit so vielen Generationen, dass diese inzwischen von Geburt an angewachsen sind.
column9:
Un drôle de membre de la famille des Grouilles, qui se bat à coups de cornes...

Portant le turban depuis toujours, elles naissent maintenant avec un turban sur la tête!
column10:
Excéntrico ejemplar de la familia de las Burbujas. Usa sus cuernos para atacar.

Han llevado gorro durante generaciones y ahora crecen en sus cabezas desde que nacen.
column11:
Un eccentrico membro della specie Blob, che usa le corna per attaccare...

I cappelli di stoffa, indossati da generazioni, ormai crescono in testa a questi esseri fin dalla nascita.
column12:
버블 종족 중 별난 멤버로 뿔을 이용하여 공격한다...

이들의 뿔은 태어나면서 머리 위에서 자라게 된다.
column13:
バーブルの種の変なメンバー、角を使って攻撃する。

布の帽子を何世代にもわたってかぶってきたため、生まれてから頭の上から生えるようになった。
column14:
An eccentric member of the Burble species which uses its horns to attack...

Their cloth hats have been worn for so many generations, they now grow atop their heads from birth.
column15:
An eccentric member of the Burble species which uses its horns to attack...

Their cloth hats have been worn for so many generations, they now grow atop their heads from birth.
column16:
Um membro excêntrico da espécie Borbulha que usa seus chifres para atacar...

Seus chapéus de tecido já foram usados por tantas gerações, que agora crescem em suas cabeças desde o nascimento.

column6:
These elusive critters shoot a powerful ray of fire from their single eye, and are able to teleport over short distances...

When injured, the Cyclops will split into two - double the danger.
column7:
These elusive critters shoot a powerful ray of fire from their single eye, and are able to teleport over short distances...

When injured, the Cyclops will split into two - double the danger.
column8:
Diese flinken Tierchen schießen einen Feuerstrahl aus ihrem Auge und können sich über kurze Entfernungen teleportieren...

Ein verwundeter Zyklop teilt sich und wird somit doppelt gefährlich.
column9:
L'œil unique de ces créatures insaisissables émet un puissant rayon de feu. Elles pratiquent la téléportation sur de courtes distances...

Blessé, le Cyclope se dédouble. Double danger!
column10:
Escurridizas criaturas de un solo ojo, desde el que lanzan un potente rayo de fuego. Pueden teletransportarse a cortas distancias.

Cuando está herido, el Cíclope se divide en dos. ¡Doble peligro!
column11:
Queste elusive creature proiettano un raggio infuocato dal loro unico occhio e possono teletrasportarsi a breve distanza...

Quando sono feriti, i Ciclopi si dividono in due, raddoppiando il pericolo.
column12:
이 잡기어려운 벌레들은 그들의 외눈에서 강력한 광선을 쏘며 짧은 거리의 텔레포트가 가능하다...

상처를 입으면 싸이클롭스는 두 개로 나뉘어져서 위험이 배가 된다.
column13:
この回避的なモンスターは目から強力な炎の光線を放つ、さらに短距離でテレポートできる…

傷つけられると、キュクロプスは２つに分かれる；危険は倍増した。
column14:
These elusive critters shoot a powerful ray of fire from their single eye, and are able to teleport over short distances...

When injured, the Cyclops will split into two - double the danger.
column15:
These elusive critters shoot a powerful ray of fire from their single eye, and are able to teleport over short distances...

When injured, the Cyclops will split into two - double the danger.
column16:

column6:
Has a suicidal defense method that involves creating an explosive charge before launching at its target and detonating...

This can be advantageous when releasing captured Slim Burbles towards obstacles.
column7:
Has a suicidal defence method that involves creating an explosive charge before launching at its target and detonating...

This can be advantageous when releasing captured Slim Burbles towards obstacles.
column8:
Verteidigt sich durch Selbstmord. Erzeugt hierfür eine Sprengladung und wirft sich auf den Gegner...

Dies kann hilfreich sein, wenn man sie gegen Hindernisse laufen lässt.
column9:
Dispose d'une tactique de défense suicidaire: elle crée une charge explosive, puis se lance sur sa cible et explose...

Pratique: pour éliminer des obstacles, il suffit de lâcher des Filigrouilles!
column10:
Tiene un sistema defensivo suicida: crea una carga explosiva antes de lanzarse al objetivo y saltar en mil pedazos.

Esto puede resultar ventajoso si se liberan Burbujas esbeltas capturadas contra obstáculos.
column11:
Usa un metodo difensivo suicida: crea una carica esplosiva e poi si lancia verso il bersaglio, esplodendo...

Lo si può sfruttare lanciando i Blob esili catturati verso gli ostacoli.
column12:
폭발력을 모아서 목표물에 돌진한다...

이 점을 이용하여 포획한 슬림 버블들을 장애물 앞에 놓으면 유용하게 쓸 수 있을 것이다.
column13:
このモンスターは自殺的な防御として爆発する。まず爆発物を作って、そして目標へ向かって跳躍して爆発する…

捕まえたスリム・バーブルを放つと、これは役に立つかもしれない
column14:
Has a suicidal defense method that involves creating an explosive charge before launching at its target and detonating...

This can be advantageous when releasing captured Slim Burbles towards obstacles.
column15:
Has a suicidal defense method that involves creating an explosive charge before launching at its target and detonating...

This can be advantageous when releasing captured Slim Burbles towards obstacles.
column16:
Possui um mecanismo de defesa suicida que envolve criar um impulso explosivo antes de se lançar contra sua vítima e explodir...

Isso pode ser vantajoso quando soltar Borbulhas Esguias capturadas em direção a obstáculos.

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>From the moment they are born, Goofy Lizards are clumsy, forgetful but ultimately good-natured. Known to spend many hours futilely attacking their own shadow.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>From the moment they are born, Goofy Lizards are clumsy, forgetful but ultimately good-natured. Known to spend many hours futilely attacking their own shadow.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Von Geburt an sind Trottelechsen ungeschickt und vergesslich, aber ungeheuer gutmütig. Bekannt dafür, dass sie stundenlang ihren eigenen Schatten zu fangen versuchen.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Les Dingolézards sont maladroits, distraits, mais profondément gentils. Ils peuvent passer des heures à se battre contre leur ombre.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Desde su nacimiento, los Lagartos bobos son torpes, olvidadizos, pero buenos por naturaleza. Pasan mucho tiempo atacando a su propia sombra sin resultado.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Fin dalla nascita, le Lucertole goffe sono rozze, smemorate ma sostanzialmente benevole. Si sa che perdono intere ore ad attaccare le loro ombre.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>얼빠진 도마뱀들은 서투르고 건망증이 있지만 사실은 온순한 생물이다. 언제나 자신의 그림자를 쫓으며 시간을 보낸다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>生まれてからバカらしいトカゲは不器用で忘れっぽいが、それにもかかわらず優しい。何時間も自分の影を追いかけることで知られている。<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>From the moment they are born, Goofy Lizards are clumsy, forgetful but ultimately good-natured. Known to spend many hours futilely attacking their own shadow.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column15: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>From the moment they are born, Goofy Lizards are clumsy, forgetful but ultimately good-natured. Known to spend many hours futilely attacking their own shadow.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Desde o momento em que nascem, os Lagartos Patetas são desastrados, esquecidos mas de boa índole. É conhecido por passar horas atacando a própria sombra.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6:
The name Half Brute understates the nature of these aggressive two-legged monsters...

While their unwieldy gait makes them slow, they are capable of stomping the ground with enough force to send a powerful shockwave into all those around.
column7:
The name Half Brute understates the nature of these aggressive two-legged monsters...

While their unwieldy gait makes them slow, they are capable of stomping the ground with enough force to send a powerful shockwave into all those around.
column8:
Der Name des Halbstarken beschreibt diese aggressiven Zweibeiner nicht annähernd...

Sie sind zwar langsam, können aber so fest aufstampfen, dass sie eine Schockwelle in ihrer Umgebung verbreiten.
column9:
Le nom de Semibrutos est bien trop doux pour ces bipèdes agressifs...

S'ils ont la démarche pesante et maladroite, ils peuvent frapper le sol si violemment qu'une onde de choc secoue tout leur environnement.
column10:
Su nombre evidencia la naturaleza de estos agresivos monstruos de dos patas.

Caminan lentos por su pesado modo de andar, aunque son capaces de pisar con tal fuerza la tierra que provocan una potente onda expansiva a su alrededor.
column11:
Il nome Mezzobruto non rende bene la natura di questi aggressivi mostri bipedi...

Anche se la loro andatura è lenta e stentata, sanno colpire il terreno con forza tale da proiettare una potente onda d'urto verso ogni creatura vicina.
column12:
반수라는 이름은 이 괴물들의 공격성을 과소평가하는 것이다...

뚱뚱하여 느리게 걷지만 강한 힘으로 땅을 내리쳐서 강력한 충격파를 낼 수 있다.
column13:
ハーフブルートと呼ばれているが、この二本足のモンスターは本当にアグレッシブ…

変な歩き型をしているせいでちょっと遅いが、地面を踏みつけることで衝撃波を作れる。

column6:
Watch out for these undead axe-wielding warriors...

They can use their weapon as a boomerang, and can even call upon a protective shield which encases them until their axe returns.
column7:

column8:
Pass auf diese untoten Axtschwinger auf...

Sie benutzen ihre Axt als Bumerang und erzeugen so einen Schutzschild, solange die Axt ihre Flugbahn beschreibt.
column9:
Méfie-toi de ces guerriers aux coups de hache mortels...

Ils peuvent utiliser leur arme comme un boomerang et invoquer un bouclier les protégeant jusqu'au retour de leur hache.
column10:
Ten cuidado con esos guerreros muertos vivientes.

Pueden usar sus armas como un bumerán e incluso utilizar un escudo protector que les recubre cuando el hacha regresa a ellos.
column11:
Stai attento a questi guerrieri non-morti armati d'ascia...

Possono usare l'arma come boomerang e perfino creare uno scudo protettivo che li protegge finché l'ascia non torna indietro.
column12:
도끼를 휘두르는 언데드 용사들을 조심하라...

이들은 그들의 무기를 부메랑으로 사용할 수 있고 그 도끼가 돌아올 때까지 보호방패 안에 숨을 수도 있다.
column13:
このアンデッドな斧振るっている武士に気をつけて…

武器をブーメランとして使用する上に、魔法の盾を呼び出して、斧が戻るまで無敵状態になる。

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Almost-A-Bull is named so not only for the two horns atop its head, but also for its unnerving habit of charging and attacking anyone wearing the color red.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Almost-A-Bull is named so not only for the two horns atop its head, but also for its unnerving habit of charging and attacking anyone wearing the colour red.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Der Fast-Ein-Stier heißt nicht nur wegen seiner zwei Hörner so. Er greift außerdem jeden an, der in der Farbe Rot gekleidet ist.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Le Pseudotoro tient son nom de ses deux cornes, bien sûr, mais également d'une sale manie: celle de charger les êtres vêtus de rouge!<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Se le conoce como Semitoro no sólo por los dos cuernos que tiene en la cabeza, sino por su desconcertante costumbre de atacar a cualquiera que vista de color rojo.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Il nome Quasitoro è dovuto non solo alle due corna in testa, ma anche alla pericolosa abitudine di caricare e attaccare chiunque indossi qualcosa di rosso.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>올모스트-어-불은 머리에 있는 두 뿔만이 아니라 빨강을 입고 있는 것은 돌진하여 공격하는 겁나는 버릇 때문에 이름이 주어졌다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>ほとんどブールの名前の元は頭の上の二本の角だけではなく、赤い服を着ている人へ追いかけて攻撃する傾向も。<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Almost-A-Bull is named so not only for the two horns atop its head, but also for its unnerving habit of charging and attacking anyone wearing the color red.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column15: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Almost-A-Bull is named so not only for the two horns atop its head, but also for its unnerving habit of charging and attacking anyone wearing the color red.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Quase-Um-Touro é chamado assim não só pelos dois chifres em sua cabeça, mas também por seu hábito intimidante de correr para atacar qualquer um vestindo a cor vermelha.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>They may be undead, but they're definitely unfriendly. Will swoop down beak first into anything they perceive as a threat.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>They may be undead, but they're definitely unfriendly. Will swoop down beak first into anything they perceive as a threat.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Sie sind ebenso untot, wie unfreundlich. Sie stürzen sich auf alles, was ihnen als Bedrohung erscheint.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Morts vivants, sans doute. Très méchants, c'est sûr. Ils foncent, bec en tête, sur la moindre menace.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Serán muertos vivientes, pero definitivamente son poco amistosos. Se lanzarán en picado y atacarán a quien consideren una amenaza.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Pur essendo non-morti, sono decisamente poco amichevoli e si buttano in picchiata per beccare chi viene percepito come una minaccia.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>이들은 언데드이며 비우호적 존재이다. 위협이라고 느끼는 것에게 일단 부리로 내칠 것이다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>このモンスターはアンデッドで、本当に攻撃的。脅威と思われるものへ急降下して、くちばしで攻撃する。<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>They may be undead, but they're definitely unfriendly. Will swoop down beak first into anything they perceive as a threat.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column15: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>They may be undead, but they're definitely unfriendly. Will swoop down beak first into anything they perceive as a threat.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>They may be undead, but they're definitely unfriendly. Will swoop down beak first into anything they perceive as a threat.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Featherless Turkey is aptly named for its total lack of plumage. Widely regarded as a delicacy at any feast during the winter season.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Featherless Turkey is aptly named for its total lack of plumage. Widely regarded as a delicacy at any feast during the winter season.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Der Nackte Truthahn trägt seinen passenden Namen aus Mangel an Federn. Im Winter ist er eine beliebte Delikatesse.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Le Dindon déplumé, comme son nom l'indique, est totalement dépourvu de plumage. Considéré comme un mets de luxe prisé à la saison froide.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Se le conoce así por su falta de plumaje. Muy apreciado como delicatessen en cualquier banquete en época invernal.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Il Tacchino spiumato si chiama così proprio perché non ha piume. È considerato una leccornia per qualsiasi festa invernale.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>깃털 없는 칠면조는 깃털이 하나도 없어서 지어진 것이다. 동절기 잔치에 별미로 쓰인다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>名前の通り、羽なし七面鳥には羽毛がない。冬の祭りの珍味として広く認められている。<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Featherless Turkey is aptly named for its total lack of plumage. Widely regarded as a delicacy at any feast during the winter season.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column15: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Featherless Turkey is aptly named for its total lack of plumage. Widely regarded as a delicacy at any feast during the winter season.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>O Peru Depenado é apropriadamente chamado assim por sua total falta de plumagem. Amplamente considerado como uma iguaria em qualquer banquete feito na temporada de inverno.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6:
The Shuttlecock Bird may be one-legged, but it's quick on its foot...

When hurtling through the air to attack it resembles an arrow, and can cause as much damage.
column7:
The Shuttlecock Bird may be one-legged, but it's quick on its foot...

When hurtling through the air to attack it resembles an arrow, and can cause as much damage.
column8:
Der Federballvogel hat zwar nur ein Bein, ist aber trotzdem sehr schnell...

Bei einem Angriff gleicht er einem Pfeil und kann auch entsprechenden Schaden anrichten.
column9:
Unijambiste, l'Aérotruche n'en est pas moins rapide...

Lorsqu'elle attaque, elle fend l'air telle une flèche, rapide, précise et dangereuse.
column10:
El Pájaro volante sólo tiene una pata, aunque es verdaderamente rápido.

Cuando vuela a toda velocidad parece una flecha y puede causar mucho daño.
column11:
L'Uccello volano, anche se ha una sola zampa, si muove in fretta...

Quando si butta in picchiata per attaccare sembra una freccia e può provocare danni notevoli.
column12:
셔틀콕 새는 다리가 하나지만 매우 빠르다...

공중을 날아갈 때는 다트 같아 보이며, 상당한 위력이 있다.
column13:
シャトルコックの鳥は一本脚のに、実はとても速い…

空中で攻撃する時、矢のように見えて、矢と同じぐらいのダメージを与える。
column14:

When hurtling through the air to attack it resembles an arrow, and can cause as much damage.

column6: The Mummy Eagle is one of the largest birds around. Undead, they are even more resilient to their live counterparts from attack.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: The Mummy Eagle is one of the largest birds around. Undead, they are even more resilient to their live counterparts from attack.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: Die Adlermumie ist einer der größten Vögel. Da sie untot sind, schaden ihnen Angriffe weniger als ihren lebenden Artgenossen.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: L'Aigle momie est le plus grand des oiseaux. Mort vivant, il est plus résistant aux attaques que l'aigle en chair et en os.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: El Águila momia es uno de los pájaros más grandes conocidos. Son muertos vivientes. Más resistentes a rivales con vida en combate.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: L'Aquila mummia è uno dei più grandi uccelli in circolazione. È non-morta ed è più resistente agli attacchi della sua controparte viva.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: 독수리 미이라는 가장 큰 새 중 하나이다. 언데드지만 살아있는 상대보다 더욱 생기 있다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: ミイライーグルはこの周りのもっとも大きい鳥の１つ。アンデッドであるため、生きているイーグルよりも多くの攻撃を耐えることができる。<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Knives Cats quickly confuse opponents with deft leaps and bounds, before plunging in to attack with alarming speed, razor sharp claws fully extended.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Knives Cats quickly confuse opponents with deft leaps and bounds, before plunging in to attack with alarming speed, razor sharp claws fully extended.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Messerkatzen verwirren ihre Gegner mit flinken Sprüngen, bevor sie mit ihren scharfen Krallen angreifen.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Le Fauvalame perturbe son adversaire en bondissant dans tous les sens avant de lancer une attaque plongeante ultra-rapide, toutes griffes dehors.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>El Gato afilado confunde a sus oponentes con hábiles saltos y brincos antes de lanzarse al ataque a gran velocidad y con las garras afiladas por delante.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>I Gatti con lame disorientano i nemici con i loro balzi e poi attaccano a velocità paurosa con gli affilatissimi artigli snodati.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>나이프 고양이들은 뛰어난 도약과 반동으로 적들을 혼돈시켜서 번개같이 적에게 날카로운 발톱공격을 한다.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Crabhands attack their enemies with sharp claws in a somewhat cumbersome fashion. Let it get close enough, however, and expect painful results.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Crabhands attack their enemies with sharp claws in a somewhat cumbersome fashion. Let it get close enough, however, and expect painful results.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Krabbenhände greifen ihre Gegner auf plumpe Art mit scharfen Krallen an. Wenn sie jedoch nah genug herankommen, sind die Resultate beachtlich.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Lorsqu'il se bat, le Matoucrabe agite ses pinces avec maladresse. Mais l'imprudent qui s'approche de trop près risque de s'en souvenir!<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Atacan a sus enemigos con afiladas garras de forma torpe y pesada. Pero si se acercan lo suficiente, el resultado será muy doloroso.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>I Gatti con chele attaccano i nemici con affilate chele. Sembrano goffi ma, se si avvicinano a sufficienza, il risultato è doloroso.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>크랩핸드들은 약간 귀찮은 방법으로 적을 공격한다. 그러나 근처에 오게 되면 고통을 감수해야만 할 것이다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6:
Sharpbeaks carry a sword in each hand which they wield with disorientating and discerning skill...

Infamous for slowly but surely bearing down on their opponent, utilizing the Florentine dual rapier method to deadly effect.
column7:
Sharpbeaks carry a sword in each hand which they wield with disorientating and discerning skill...

Infamous for slowly but surely bearing down on their opponent, utilizing the Florentine dual rapier method to deadly effect.
column8:
Spitzschnäbel tragen in jeder Hand ein Schwert, womit sie sehr geschickt umgehen können...

Aufgrund des langsamen, aber qualvollen Todes, den sie ihren Gegnern bescheren, sind sie sehr unbeliebt.
column9:
Le Musopik porte une épée dans chaque main qu'il manie avec une habileté et une vitesse déconcertante...

Excellant dans le combat à la florentine, il met à mort sa victime lentement mais sûrement.
column10:
Los Picofinos llevan una espada en cada mano que empuñan de forma espectacular y desconcertante.

De mala fama por su lentitud, son capaces de derribar a cualquier oponente con el letal efecto de la doble estocada florentina.
column11:
I Becchi acuminati hanno una spada in ogni mano e le brandiscono entrambe con abilità, confondendo i nemici...

Sono noti per logorare lentamente i nemici, usando con terribile efficacia la tecnica fiorentina del doppio stocco.
column12:
날카로운 부리들은 양손에 칼을 쥐고 있으며 적들 헷갈리게 만들어 공격을 한다...

느리지만 적들에게 확실히 적을 압도하는 것으로 악명 높다.

column6:
Skull Worshippers use their flaming staffs and ability to summon ghostly flying skulls to deadly effect...

Encounter one of these and the forces of evil are bound to be close by.
column7:
Skull Worshippers use their flaming staffs to attack their foe to deadly effect...

Encounter one of these and the forces of evil are bound to be close by.
column8:
Schädelanbeter benutzen im Kampf ihre Flammenstäbe und beschwören fliegende Geisterschädel...

Wenn du auf einen von ihnen triffst, dann sind die Mächte des Bösen nicht weit.
column9:
Doté de son bâton de feu, l'Adorateur de Crânes invoque de fantomatiques crânes volants à des fins mortelles...

Lorsqu'il rôde, les forces du mal ne sont jamais très loin.
column10:
Usan bastones ardientes y pueden invocar a fantasmagóricas calaveras volantes de mortales efectos.

Si tropiezas con uno, no hay duda de que las fuerzas del Mal andan cerca.
column11:
Gli Adoratori Teschi sfruttano le loro aste fiammeggianti per creare spettrali e pericolosi teschi volanti...

Se ne incontri uno, allora le forze del male sono all'opera nei paraggi.
column12:
해골 숭배자들은 화염 지팡이와 유령 같은 나는 해골들을 소환할 수 있는 능력을 이용하여 공격해 올 것이다...

이들 중 하나를 만난다면 분명이 근처에 해골 숭배자들이 있을 것이다.
column13:

column6:
Able to pass through solid forms, they move with the swiftness of a winter cloud and attack as if from nowhere...

Save projectile weaponry for elsewhere, as they will pass straight through the Dark Worshipper.
column7:
Able to pass through solid forms, they move with the swiftness of a winter cloud and attack as if from nowhere...

Save projectile weaponry for elsewhere, as they will pass straight through the Dark Worshipper.
column8:
Sie können sich durch feste Materie bewegen, sind schnell wie eine Winterwolke und scheinen aus dem Nichts anzugreifen...

Schusswaffen können hier nicht viel ausrichten.
column9:
Capable de traverser des corps solides, il se déplace subrepticement et surprend par ses attaques...

Ne gaspille pas tes projectiles, ils ne peuvent rien contre l'Adorateur obscur!
column10:
Pueden atravesar formas sólidas y se mueven con la rapidez de una nube de tormenta. Su ataque parece surgir de la nada.

Guarda tus armas para otro momento, ya que no te servirán de nada contra el Adorador oscuro.
column11:
Possono attraversare gli oggetti solidi, si muovono velocemente e attaccano direzioni impreviste...

Risparmia le armi da lancio per altri mostri, perché attraversano gli Adoratori Tenebre senza fare loro nulla.
column12:
벽을 통과할 수 있고 빠르게 움직여서 알 수 없는 곳에서 공격한다...

발사 공격은 통하지 않는다. 그런 공격은 이 어둠의 숭배자들을 그냥 통과하기 때문이다.

column6:
In addition to their well-honed swordsmanship, they are capable of releasing an evil, shimmering skull that chases down an opponent...

A flurry of blows often fails to harm them, such is their defensive skill.
column7:
In addition to their well-honed swordsmanship, they are capable of releasing an evil, shimmering skull that chases down an opponent...

A flurry of blows often fails to harm them, such is their defensive skill.
column8:
Sie können äußerst gut mit dem Schwert umgehen und beschwören Totenschädel, die ihre Gegner jagen...

Sie sind gut in der Verteidigung und daher schwer zu treffen.
column9:
Ils maîtrisent l'art de manier l'épée et lâchent des crânes vibrant de toute la puissance du mal pour écraser leurs adversaires...

Ils peuvent se montrer très résistants aux rafales, même les plus violentes.
column10:
Además de su enorme destreza en el manejo de la espada, son capaces de liberar una calavera maligna que dé caza a su oponente.

A menudo, los aluviones de golpes no les afectan, gracias a su habilidad defensiva.
column11:
Oltre a saper maneggiare molto bene la spada, possono evocare un teschio scintillante, capace di inseguire un avversario...

La loro abilità di difesa è tale che spesso neppure una raffica di colpi riesce a toccarli.
column12:
뛰어난 검술로 적들을 쫓는 악마성의 빛나는 해골.

연속공격을 하면 방어 하는 경우도 있으니 주의하라.

column6:
They rear up out of their holes with alarming speed, using their great mass to slam down, crushing anything beneath...

Known to be impervious to anything that might stun smaller monsters.
column7:

Known to be impervious to anything that might stun smaller monsters.
column8:
Sie kommen blitzschnell aus ihren Löchern und überwältigen alles und jeden mit ihrer Masse...

Sie sind unempfindlich gegen alles, was ein kleineres Monster aufhalten könnte.
column9:
Il surgit de son trou à une vitesse sidérante, exploitant sa masse imposante pour tout écraser sur son passage...

Il résiste aux armes utilisées contre les monstres de moindre envergure.
column10:
Salen de sus madrigueras con alarmante velocidad y utilizan su enorme volumen para atacar. Lo aplastan a su paso.

Tienen fama de ser inmunes a todo lo que aturde a pequeños monstruos.
column11:
Si lanciano a grande velocità dalle loro tane, sfruttando la massa per piombare a terra e schiacciare ciò che colpiscono...

Sono invulnerabili a tutto ciò che potrebbe stordire mostri più piccoli.
column12:
이들은 구멍에서 놀랄만한 속도로 뛰어 나오며 육중한 몸으로 깔아뭉겐다...

어리숙한 공격으로는 통하지 않을 것이다.

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Blade Scorpion is quick on its feet and quicker to attack. Be wary of its tail, and the darkened hidey holes it favors for sleeping.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Blade Scorpion is quick on its feet and quicker to attack. Be wary of its tail, and the darkened hidey holes it favours for sleeping.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Der Säbelskorpion kann schnell laufen und noch schneller angreifen. Von seinen dunklen Schlafhöhlen sollte man sich fernhalten.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Le Scorpiserpe court vite et attaque plus vite encore. Attention à sa queue et aux trous dans lesquels il se réfugie!<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>El Escorpión cuchilla se mueve y ataca con mucha rapidez. Cuidado con su cola y con los oscuros escondrijos que utiliza para dormir.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Lo Scorpione-falce si muove velocemente e attacca ancora più velocemente. Attento alla sua coda e agli oscuri anfratti nascosti dove ama riposare.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>칼날 전갈은 움직임도 빠르지만 공격은 더 빠르다. 녀석들이 즐겨 잠을 자는 어두운 구멍들을 조심하라.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Blade Scorpion is quick on its feet and quicker to attack. Be wary of its tail, and the darkened hidey holes it favors for sleeping.<ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>

column6:
The Tacked Spider likes to hang around all sorts of places...

Keep an eye out on the ceilings of any cavernous tunnel in case one drops down from above.
column7:

Keep an eye out on the ceilings of any cavernous tunnel in case one drops down from above.
column8:
Die Stelzenspinne findet sich so ziemlich überall...

Achte immer auf Höhlendecken, da sie sich gerne von dort herunterfallen lassen.
column9:
La Migagile a le don d'ubiquité...

Jette un œil au plafond des sombres tunnels: elle pourrait te guetter!
column10:
A la Araña hilandera le gusta engancharse en cualquier lugar.

Vigila las bóvedas en los túneles de las cavernas por si alguna se deja caer.
column11:
Il Ragno impalato ama appendersi a qualsiasi cosa...

Attento al tetto di qualsiasi galleria o caverna: potrebbe caderne uno dall'alto.
column12:
붙어있는 거미는 이곳 저곳에 걸려 있는 것을 좋아한다...

이들이 위에서 떨어질 수 있으니 동굴이 많은 터널에서는 천장을 주의하라.

column6:
Jumps and clings to its prey, biting away with exceptional persistence until either shaken off or well fed...

Encounter one and others are sure to be close by, as they hunt in groups.
column7:
Jumps and clings to its prey, biting away with exceptional persistence until either shaken off or well fed...

Encounter one and others are sure to be close by, as they hunt in groups.
column8:
Springt die Beute an und beißt sich durch, bis sie abgeschüttelt wird oder satt ist...

Eine kommt selten allein, da sie in Gruppen jagen.
column9:
Elle saute sur sa proie et s'y cramponne pour la mordre violemment, puis la dévore sans laisser une seule miette.

Si tu en rencontres une, méfiance, elle chasse en groupe.
column10:
Salta y agarra a su presa, a la que pica con una perseverancia excepcional hasta que la deshecha o se la come.

Si tropiezas con alguna, ten por seguro que habrá más, ya que cazan en grupo.
column11:
Salta e afferra la preda, mordendola con tenacia fino a quando non viene scacciato o si è saziato...

Se ne incontri uno, ce ne saranno sicuramente altri nei paraggi, perché cacciano in gruppo.
column12:
적에게 달라붙은 후, 흔들어 떨어 뜨리기 전까지는 물고 놓지 않는다....

이들은 무리로 사냥하기 때문에 하나가 보이면 반드시 동료들이 주위에 있을 것이다.

column6:
An arthropod with the ability to move swiftly along vertical and horizontal surfaces...

The vicious fangs are not the only thing to fear; each of its legs ends in lethal, dagger-like claws.
column7:

column8:
Ein Gliederfüßer, der an Wänden und Decken laufen kann...

Die gefährlichen Fänge sind nicht das einzige, was man bei ihnen fürchten muss. Ihre Beine enden in tödlichen dolchartigen Krallen.
column9:
Arthropode se déplaçant avec agilité sur les plans horizontaux et verticaux...

Si ses crochets sont dangereux, l'extrémité de ses pattes - poignards aiguisés - est également mortelle.
column10:
Artrópodo que puede moverse con rapidez en superficies horizontales y verticales.

Sus colmillos afilados no son lo único a tener en cuenta: los extremos de sus patas poseen garras como puñales.
column11:
Artropode capace di muoversi velocemente sulle superfici verticali e orizzontali...

Le terribili zanne non sono l'unica cosa da temere: le zampe terminano in micidiali artigli simili a pugnali.
column12:
어디에서나 빠르게 움직일 수 있는 능력을 가진 절지동물...

지독한 이빨뿐만이 아니라 다리 끝부분에도 날카로운 발톱이 나 있다.

column6:

Ihr einzigartiger Körper macht sie unempfindlich gegen Kälte.
column9:
Si sa démarche prête à rire, sa morsure n'a rien de drôle. Aussi menaçant sur terre que dans l'eau...

Son métabolisme unique le rend extrêmement résistant au froid.
column10:
Su modo de caminar puede resultar cómico, pero su mordedura no lo es. Son implacables en tierra y agua.

Su extraordinario metabolismo las hace inmunes al frío.
column11:
I loro movimenti possono sembrare buffi, ma il loro morso non lo è. Sono da temere sia sulla terraferma sia in acqua...

Il loro metabolismo li rende insensibili al freddo.
column12:
걷는 모습은 우스워 보이지만 그들이 무는 힘은 대단하다. 사나운 성격이다...

이들의 추위도 잘 견딘다고 한다.

column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Exo-Piranha is a new evolutionary strain of Piranha. Only discovered in recent years, they are faster and stronger than others of their species.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Der Exo-Piranha ist ein verwandter des Piranhas. Er wurde erst vor wenigen Jahren entdeckt und ist stärker und schneller als der Rest seiner Art.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>L'Exo-Piranha est une toute nouvelle variété de Piranha. Récemment découvert, il est plus fort et plus rapide que le restant de l'espèce.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>La Exopiraña es la evolución de la especie Piraña. Se ha descubierto hace poco. Es más rápida y fuerte que otras especies de la misma familia.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Il Piranha corazzato è una nuova evoluzione del Piranha. È stato scoperto di recente ed è più forte e veloce delle altre specie.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>견갑 피라냐는 파라나가 진화한 새로운 종이다. 최근에 들어서야 발견 되었으며, 다른 종류들보다 빠르고 강하다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

Electric Eels are aggressive and territorial creatures, and in large quantities have been known to electrify vast areas of water.

Ein schlangengleicher Fisch, der elektrische Ladungen abgeben kann.

Elektrische Aale sind aggressiv und ortsgebunden. In größeren Schwärmen können sie sogar riesige Wassergebiete unter Strom setzen.
column9:
Poisson serpentiforme émettant des décharges électriques.

Les Anguilles électriques sont des animaux territoriaux et agressifs qui électrisent leurs eaux.
column10:
Pez con forma de serpiente capaz de emitir descargas eléctricas.

Son criaturas agresivas y territoriales y, en grandes grupos, puede electrificar enormes zonas acuáticas.
column11:
Pesce simile a un serpente capace di emettere scariche elettriche.

La Lampreda è aggressiva e difende il suo territorio. In grandi banchi può elettrificare anche grossi specchi d'acqua.
column12:
뱀 같은 물고기로 전기를 방출 한다.

Ein großer, essbarer Meeresfisch, den man an seinem flachen Körper und seinem grazilen Schwimmstil erkennt.

Aufgrund seiner Begehrtheit als Delikatesse ist der Mantarochen inzwischen sehr misstrauisch gegenüber jedem, der ihm zu nahe kommt.

Gros poisson de mer comestible remarquable par la grâce de ses mouvements et son corps plat.

La délicatesse de sa chair recherchée a rendu cette créature très méfiante.
column10:
Pez grande y comestible característico por su cuerpo plano y su estilo elegante.

Muchos años de tradición culinaria la han convertido en una criatura cautelosa con cualquier cosa que se acerque demasiado a ella.
column11:
Un grosso pesce commestibile, noto per il corpo piatto e l'aggraziato stile natatorio.

Dopo anni di sfruttamento culinario, questa creatura è diventata comprensibilmente poco amichevole verso chiunque si avvicini troppo.
column12:

오랫동안 요리재료로 사용되며 가까이 다가가면 놀라 달아난다.

Moving with great ease, they often attack their prey before they've even been spotted.

Der Stachelfisch ist schnell und verteidigt sein Territorium äußerst aggressiv. Daher ist er eine beliebte Zutat in Wassergräben von Anwesen.

Er greift sein Opfer meistens schon an, bevor er entdeckt wird.
column9:
Rapide et jaloux de son territoire, le Poisson d'or est apprécié par les riches qui en remplissent leurs étangs pour éloigner les visiteurs indésirables.

Se déplaçant avec une grande facilité, il attaque avant même d'avoir été remarqué.
column10:
Nadador rápido y protector de su territorio. Es a menudo elegido por la clase alta, que los utilizan en fosos aún más peligrosos para los intrusos.

Se mueven con mucha facilidad y son capaces de atacar a su presa incluso antes de ser vistos.
column11:
Il Pesce trombetta è veloce e protegge accanitamente il suo territorio. Viene spesso scelto dai nobili per rendere i loro fossati ancora più pericolosi per gli intrusi.

Si muove molto agilmente e spesso riesce a cogliere le sue prede di sorpresa.
column12:
빠르게 헤엄치며 자신의 영역을 지키는 척추물고기는 종종 고위층에서 자신의 경비를 위해 기르기도 한다.

유연하게 움직이면서 적들이 감지하기도 전에 공격한다.

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Tree Creature may possess a beautiful magical ability, but let the phosphorescent glow enchant you and you'll get a nasty surprise from below.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Tree Creature may possess a beautiful magical ability, but let the phosphorescent glow enchant you and you'll get a nasty surprise from below.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Das Baumtier besitzt ein wunderschönes, magisches Talent, aber wenn man sich davon verzaubern lässt, folgt meistens eine böse Überraschung.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>L'Arbre magique possède une aptitude magique d'une grande beauté - mais si tu te laisses captiver par sa phosphorescence, gare à toi!<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Puede que esta criatura posea una habilidad mágica maravillosa, pero si te dejas encantar por su brillo, una desagradable sorpresa te llegará desde abajo.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>La Creatura Albero possiede una stupenda abilità magica, ma se ti farai affascinare dalla sua luce fosforescente, riceverai una brutta sorpresa dal basso.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>나무 생물은 아름다운 마법의 힘을 가지고 있으며 인광의 빛으로 마법을 걸어서 밑에서 기습을 한다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Tree Creature may possess a beautiful magical ability, but let the phosphorescent glow enchant you and you'll get a nasty surprise from below.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Tree Creature may possess a beautiful magical ability, but let the phosphorescent glow enchant you and you'll get a nasty surprise from below.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column15: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Tree Creature may possess a beautiful magical ability, but let the phosphorescent glow enchant you and you'll get a nasty surprise from below.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A Criatura Arbórea pode possuir uma bela habilidade mágica, mas deixe o brilho fosforescente encantá-lo e receberá uma surpresa desagradável por baixo.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Sunflower is not as peaceful as it may sound. Get hit by any one of the spores it emits and you won't be sleeping well that night.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Sunflower is not as peaceful as it may sound. Get hit by any one of the spores it emits and you won't be sleeping well that night.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Die Sonnenblume ist nicht so friedlich, wie man meinen könnte. Lass dich von einem ihrer Kerne treffen, und du wirst erst einmal gut schlafen können.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Le Tournesol n'est pas aussi doux qu'il en a l'air. Si tu te fais toucher par un de ses spores, tu vas passer une nuit infernale!<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>No es tan pacífico como pueda parecer. Si te alcanza una de las esporas que lanza, no serás capaz de dormir esa noche.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Il Girasole non è pacifico come potrebbe sembrare. Se ti farai colpire da una delle spore che emana, preparati a dormire male.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>해바라기를 조심하라. 위협적인 포자 공격을 한다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Sunflower is not as peaceful as it may sound. Get hit by any one of the spores it emits and you won't be sleeping well that night.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Sunflower is not as peaceful as it may sound. Get hit by any one of the spores it emits and you won't be sleeping well that night.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column15: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Sunflower is not as peaceful as it may sound. Get hit by any one of the spores it emits and you won't be sleeping well that night.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>O Girassol não é tão pacífico quanto possa parecer. Seja atingido por um dos esporos que ele emite e você não dormirá bem naquela noite.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Slow, timid and unthreatening, Shell Critters are of little use. The bourgeoisie are known to use their shells as ornamentation.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Slow, timid and unthreatening, Shell Critters are of little use. The bourgeoisie are known to use their shells as ornamentation.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Schalentierchen sind langsam, ängstlich und von geringem Nutzen. Die Reichen benutzen ihre Schalen gerne als Zierde.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Lent, timide et doux, le Coquillard n'est pas très utile. Sa coquille est très prisée par les riches qui l'utilisent en déco.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Lenta, tímida y nada amenazadora, la Bestia caparazón es de poca utilidad. La burguesía utiliza su caparazón como objeto de decoración.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Le Creature col guscio sono lente, timide e innocue. Servono a poco, ma i borghesi di solito usano i loro gusci come ornamenti.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>느리고, 순하고 조용한 껍질 괴물들은 쓸모가 거의 없다. 부자들은 이들의 껍데기를 장식으로  사용하기도 한다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Slow, timid and unthreatening, Shell Critters are of little use. The bourgeoisie are known to use their shells as ornamentation.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Slow, timid and unthreatening, Shell Critters are of little use. The bourgeoisie are known to use their shells as ornamentation.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column15: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Slow, timid and unthreatening, Shell Critters are of little use. The bourgeoisie are known to use their shells as ornamentation.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Lentas, tímidas e nada ameaçadoras, Criaturas Cascudas são pouco úteis. A burguesia é conhecida por usar seus cascos como ornamentos.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A Cobra is a venomous hooded snake which resides in trees and other plant life. Disturb a Cobra's home and it will not hesitate to rear its head and attack the intruder.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A Cobra is a venomous hooded snake which resides in trees and other plant life. Disturb a Cobra's home and it will not hesitate to rear its head and attack the intruder.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Kobras sind sehr giftig und leben auf Bäumen und anderen Pflanzen. Wer das Heim einer Kobra stört, muss mit einem sofortigen Angriff rechnen.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Le Cobra est un serpent venimeux se prélassant dans les arbres, entre autres végétaux. Ne te risque pas à déranger un Cobra, car sa réaction sera instantanée!<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>La Cobra es una serpiente venenosa que habita en los árboles u otras plantas. Si alguien la perturba, no dudará en erguir su cabeza y atacar al intruso.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Il Cobra è un serpente velenoso che vive sugli alberi o sulle piante. Se disturberai il suo attuale habitat, non esiterà a sollevare la testa e ad attaccare.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>코브라는 독을 지닌 두건모양의 뱀으로 나무가 있는 평원에서 서식한다. 자신의 영역 침범하면 이들은 바로 공격해 올 것이다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A Cobra is a venomous hooded snake which resides in trees and other plant life. Disturb a Cobra's home and it will not hesitate to rear its head and attack the intruder.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A Cobra is a venomous hooded snake which resides in trees and other plant life. Disturb a Cobra's home and it will not hesitate to rear its head and attack the intruder.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column15: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A Cobra is a venomous hooded snake which resides in trees and other plant life. Disturb a Cobra's home and it will not hesitate to rear its head and attack the intruder.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A Cobra é uma cobra encapuzada venenosa que vive em árvores e outras plantas. Incomode a casa de uma Cobra e ela não hesitará em levantar sua cabeça e atacar o intruso.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6:
Despite its overbearing size, the Spitting Toad is a placid creature renowned for its soft spot for coconuts.

Spitting Toads have been known to assist adventurers who feed them this nutty delicacy.
column7:

column8:
Trotz ihrer enormen Größe sind Spuckerkröten friedliche Wesen, deren Vorliebe für Kokosnüsse weit bekannt ist.

Man sagt, dass Spuckerkröten manchmal Abenteurern helfen, die sie mit dieser Delikatesse füttern.
column9:
Malgré sa taille, le Crapaud cracheur est une créature placide très gourmande de noix de coco.

Le Crapaud cracheur est le compagnon idéal de l'aventurier, pour peu qu'il lui donne des noix de coco.
column10:
A pesar de su dominante tamaño, el Sapo escupidor es una plácida criatura que tiene debilidad por los cocos.

Tiene fama de ayudar a los aventureros que le proporcionan este delicioso manjar.
column11:
Nonostante la taglia, il Rospo sputatore è una creatura placida che ha notoriamente un debole per le noci di cocco.

I Rospi sputatori aiutano i viandanti che offrono loro queste coriacee leccornie.
column12:
엄청난 크기에도 불구하고 이 두꺼비는 코코넛을 좋아하는 것으로 알려져 있는 조용한 생물이다.

뱉는 두꺼비들은 코코넛을 주면 탐험가들을 도와 준다고 한다.

Spitting Toads have been known to assist adventurers who feed them this nutty delicacy.
column16:
Apesar de seu tamanho autoritário, o Sapo Cuspidor é uma criatura calma conhecida por seu ponto fraco por cocos.

Sapos Cuspidores são conhecidos por ajudar aventureiros que os alimentarem com essa iguaria.

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>This frog may well be small, but it isn't the friendliest creature around. Indigenous to swamplands, they're noxious little critters.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>This frog may well be small, but it isn't the friendliest creature around. Indigenous to swamplands, they're noxious little critters.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Dieser Frosch ist zwar klein, dafür aber umso giftiger. Meistens finden sie sich in Sumpfgebieten.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Petite, mais vraiment très hargneuse. Originaire des marais, cette créature est extrêmement nocive.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Se trata de una rana pequeña, pero desde luego no es una criatura amistosa. Viven en pantanos y son criaturas dañinas.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Nonostante la piccola taglia, questa rana è poco amichevole. Vive di norma nelle paludi ed è una creatura nociva.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>이 개구리는 작지만 안전한 생물은 아니다. 늪지대에서 살고 있으며 독성을 지니고 있다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Este sapo pode ser pequeno, mas não é a criatura mais amigável por aí. Nativos dos pântanos, são criaturinhas tóxicas.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Nose Needler is a burrowing mammal found in dusty regions. Good luck to anyone attempting to land a blow on one of these evasive mammals.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Nose Needler is a burrowing mammal found in dusty regions. Good luck to anyone attempting to land a blow on one of these evasive mammals.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Der Nasenstichler ist ein Säugetier aus der Wüstengegend. Aufgrund seiner Flinkheit und seiner Grabkünste ist er kaum zu erwischen.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Le Poilagratter est un mammifère fouisseur des régions sablonneuses. Extrêmement rapide, cet animal est difficile à atteindre.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>El Provocador es un mamífero excavador que habita en regiones polvorientas. Quien intente atacar a uno de estos evasivos animales necesitará suerte.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>L'Occhiellatore è un mammifero che scava la sua tana e vive nelle regioni polverose. Auguri a chiunque cerchi di colpire queste sfuggenti creature.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>노우즈 니들러는 먼지가 많은 지역에서 발견되는 땅을 파는 포유류다. 이 녀석을 잡는기는 그리 쉽지 않을 것이다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Il exploite sa stature unique pour assommer l'adversaire à coups de tête. Ensuite, le Migasquelette peut dévorer sa proie à son aise.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>La forma de su cabeza le permite pegar cabezazos a sus presas. Tras dejarla inconsciente, la Araña esqueleto puede devorar a su presa a su gusto.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Il Ragno scheletro sfrutta la particolare altezza della testa per colpire la preda. Dopo averle fatto perdere i sensi, può divorarla a suo piacimento.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>큰머리를 이용하여 적에게 박치기를 하는 것으로 알려져 있다. 해골 거미는 적을 기절을 시킨 후에 즐겨가면서 잡아먹는다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>When alerted to a potential threat they will spin faster and faster on the spot, before dashing headlong into their enemy.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>When alerted to a potential threat they will spin faster and faster on the spot, before dashing headlong into their enemy.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Wenn sie bedroht werden, drehen sie sich zunächst auf der Stelle und stürzen sich dann auf ihren Gegner.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>En présence d'une menace, il patine de plus en plus vite avant de foncer sur l'ennemi.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Cuando advierten una amenaza potencial, giran cada vez más rápido sobre el sitio, antes de lanzarse de cabeza contra el enemigo.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Quando ha captato una potenziale minaccia, si mette a rotolare sempre più velocemente sul posto, per poi lanciarsi verso il nemico.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>위험의 가능성을 감지하면 고속회전을 하며 적에게 돌진한다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>When alerted to a potential threat they will spin faster and faster on the spot, before dashing headlong into their enemy.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Quando alertados de potenciais ameaças, eles giram cada vez mais rápido no lugar, antes de correr de cabeça até seu inimigo.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6:
Employing the same spinning and charging attack as the Skeletal Armadillo, the Skeletal Fire Armadillo also generates a ball of fire, damaging any opponents with scorching results...

Captured ones can be used to burn down wooden obstacles.
column7:

Captured ones can be used to burn down wooden obstacles.
column8:
Das Feuergürteltier erweitert den Wirbelangriff noch mit einem Feuerball, sodass der Gegner auch noch mit Verbrennungen rechnen muss...

Wenn man sie gefangen nimmt, kann man mit ihnen hölzerne Hindernisse niederbrennen.
column9:
Utilisant la même technique d'attaque que le Tatou, le Tatou de feu émet en plus des boules de feu capables de tout brûler sur leur passage...

Capturés, ils te seront utiles pour brûler les obstacles en bois.
column10:
Aunque usa el mismo ataque giratorio y de carga que el Armadillo esqueleto, el Armadillo de fuego también genera una bola ígnea que provoca abrasadores daños a los rivales.

Los capturados pueden usarse para quemar obstáculos de madera.
column11:
Sfrutta la stessa tecnica di attacco rotolante dell'Armadillo e in più lancia una sfera di fuoco che ha un effetto bruciante sui suoi avversari...

Quelli catturati si possono sfruttare per bruciare gli ostacoli di legno.
column12:
해골의 아르마딜로처럼 회전 및 기 모으기 공격을 사용하는 해골의 화염 아르마딜로는 화염공격으로 적들을 태워버린다...

포획을 한 후 이들을 이용 나무로 된 장애물을 태워버릴 수 있다.

Tatus capturados podem ser usados para queimar obstáculos de madeira.

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Skeletal Electric Armadillo spins on the spot, building up an electric charge shocking to anything that comes into contact with it.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>The Skeletal Electric Armadillo spins on the spot, building up an electric charge shocking to anything that comes into contact with it.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Das elektrische Gürteltier wirbelt auf der Stelle und lädt sich dabei elektrisch auf. Diese Ladung schützt es dann vor den Angriffen jener, die es berühren.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Le Tatou électrique patine pour accumuler une charge électrique qu'il décharge sur tout ce qu'il touche.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>El Armadillo eléctrico gira sobre el sitio y genera una carga eléctrica que electrocuta todo lo que entra en contacto con este animal.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>L'Armadillo elettrico rotola vorticosamente sul posto, accumulando una carica elettrica che stordisce qualsiasi creatura.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd> 해골의 전기 아르마딜로는 회전하면서 주위로 오는 자들에게 전기충격을 준다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>O Tatu Elétrico Esquelético gira no lugar, gerando uma carga elétrica que eletrocuta tudo que entrar em contato com ele.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>These little dogs are none too pleased about being mummified, so try not to get close. If you make that mistake, expect them to cling to you and bite away until they are shaken off.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>These little dogs are none too pleased about being mummified, so try not to get close. If you make that mistake, expect them to cling to you and bite away until they are shaken off.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Diese kleinen Hunde sind alles andere als glücklich darüber, mumifiziert zu sein. Man sollte ihnen daher nicht zu nahe kommen. Ansonsten beißen sie sich fest, bis es einem gelingt, sie abzuschütteln.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Ces petits chiens sont loin d'être heureux d'avoir été momifiés, alors ne t'en approche pas! Tu risquerais de ne plus pouvoir t'asseoir pendant un moment.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Estos pequeños perros no están muy satisfechos con su momificación; no te acerques demasiado. Si te acercas, ten en cuenta que te atacarán y te morderán hasta que te los quites de encima.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Questi piccoli cani non amano essere mummificati, quindi evita di avvicinarti. Se commetti questo errore, ti afferreranno e continueranno a morderti finché non farai loro mollare la presa.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>이 작은 개들은 미이라가 되는 것에 대해 별로 기뻐하지 않기 때문에 근처에 가지 않는 것이 좋다. 만약 실수로 다가간다면 물고 떨어지지 않을 것이다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>These little dogs are none too pleased about being mummified, so try not to get close. If you make that mistake, expect them to cling to you and bite away until they are shaken off.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>These little dogs are none too pleased about being mummified, so try not to get close. If you make that mistake, expect them to cling to you and bite away until they are shaken off.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Estes pequenos cães não estão nem um pouco contentes em terem sido mumificados, então tente manter distância. Caso cometa esse erro, espere que grudem em você e o mordam até que sejam sacudidos para longe.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>La Migaguêpe possède des griffes au dard puissant avec lesquelles elle fend l'air... et ses proies !<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A Aranha Vespa representa uma ameaça com suas afiadas garras frontais, que cortam o vento... e sua presa.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>As they are rooted to the spot they cannot see in every direction. Get behind one and, to all intents and purposes, it is completely harmless.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>As they are rooted to the spot they cannot see in every direction. Get behind one and, to all intents and purposes, it is completely harmless.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Da sie im Boden verwurzelt sind, können sie nicht in alle Richtungen schauen. Es ist also völlig harmlos, hinter ihnen zu stehen.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Fixé au sol, il ne peut voir dans toutes les directions. Passe derrière, tu ne risqueras rien.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Cuando está en tierra, no puede ver en todas direcciones. Si te colocas detrás, verás que es completamente inofensivo a todos los efectos.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Essendo bloccati dove si trovano, non possono vedere in tutte le direzioni. Se gli passi oltre, diventano totalmente innocui.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>An annoying creature which refuses to give up the chase until it's sunk its teeth into something. Most commonly found living in and around populated areas.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>An annoying creature which refuses to give up the chase until it's sunk its teeth into something. Most commonly found living in and around populated areas.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Ein nerviges Tier, das seine Jagd nicht aufgibt, bis es seine Zähne irgendwo hineingebohrt hat. Lebt meistens in der Nähe bewohnter Gebiete.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Petite créature agaçante qui chasse jusqu'à ce qu'enfin, elle puisse mordre dans quelque chose. On la trouve surtout dans les zones peuplées.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Molesta criatura que no se da por vencida hasta que no clava sus dientes en algo. Habita normalmente en áreas pobladas y sus alrededores.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Fastidiosa creatura che rifiuta di abbandonare la caccia finché non ha affondato i denti da qualche parte. Si trova soprattutto nelle zone abitate e nei dintorni.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>무언가를 물지 못고는 못 배기는 짜증나는 생물. 사람들이 많은 곳에서 흔히 발견된다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Uma criatura irritante que não desiste de uma perseguição até ter fincado seus dentes em algo. Mais comumente encontrada vivendo ao redor de áreas populadas.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A Chihuahua is a smooth-coated dog of diminutive stature. While they are highly respected by the dog loving community, most find their incessant yapping to be very irritating.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column7: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A Chihuahua is a smooth-coated dog of diminutive stature. While they are highly respected by the dog loving community, most find their incessant yapping to be very irritating.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column8: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Ein  Chihuahua ist ein kleines Tier mit weichem Fell. Bei Hundeliebhabern sind sie sehr beliebt. Bei allen anderen findet ihr Gekläffe jedoch wenig Anklang.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column9: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Un Chihuahua est un petit chien au poil doux. Si les amoureux des chiens l'adorent, le plupart des gens ne supportent pas ses jappements agaçants.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column10: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Son perros de suave pelaje y muy pequeños. Aunque muy respetados por los amantes de los perros, la mayoría considera irritante su incesante ladrido.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column11: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>Il Chihuahua è un cane a pelo raso di piccola taglia. Pur essendo rispettato dagli amanti dei cani, molti trovano irritanti i suoi continui latrati.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column12: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>치와와는 몸이 작고 부드러운 가죽을 가진 개다. 애견으로 사랑을 받지만 대부분의 사람들은 쉴 새없이 짖어대는 것을 짜증낸다.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column13: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A Chihuahua is a smooth-coated dog of diminutive stature. While they are highly respected by the dog loving community, most find their incessant yapping to be very irritating.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column14: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A Chihuahua is a smooth-coated dog of diminutive stature. While they are highly respected by the dog loving community, most find their incessant yapping to be very irritating.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column15: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>A Chihuahua is a smooth-coated dog of diminutive stature. While they are highly respected by the dog loving community, most find their incessant yapping to be very irritating.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>
column16: <ES HT_Text_ES_S_BOSStd>O Chihuahua é um cão de pelagem macia e baixa estatura. Apesar de serem altamente respeitados pela comunidade amante dos cães, a maioria das pessoas acham seu latido constante extremamente irritante.<ES HT_Text_ES_E_BOSStd>

column6:
The Big Bull would perhaps be more accurately described as a "big bully"...

It cannot be reasoned with, and will persistently swing and smash its hammer at anything it feels like bothering. Do not get in the way!
column7:
The Big Bull would perhaps be more accurately described as a "big bully"...

It cannot be reasoned with, and will persistently swing and smash its hammer at anything it feels like bothering. Do not get in the way!
column8:
Der Große Stier sollte vielleicht besser als Großer Dickkopf bezeichnet werden...

Mit Argumenten ist ihm nicht beizukommen, und er schlägt seinen Hammer auf alles, das ihm nicht passt. Ihm sollte man nicht in den Weg kommen!
column9:
Le Maxitoro porte bien son nom, c'est rien de le dire...

Impossible de discuter avec lui, il fait tournoyer son marteau et le lance sur tout ce qui bouge. Sauve-toi!
column10:
El Toro grande debería llamarse más exactamente "Gran matón"...

Es imposible razonar con él, ya que utiliza su martillo para golpear todo lo que le resulta molesto. ¡No te cruces en su camino!
column11:
Il Grande toro è anche un grande attaccabrighe...

Non è possibile ragionarci e ha l'abitudine di colpire con il suo martello qualunque cosa consideri fastidiosa. Non ti avvicinare!
column12:
거대한 황소를 더 자세히 설명자면 아마 "거대한 망나니"라고나 할까...

말도 통하지 않고 아무에게나 거칠게 망치를 휘두를 거야. 상대하지 않는 것이 좋아!
column13:
The Big Bull would perhaps be more accurately described as a "big bully"...

It cannot be reasoned with, and will persistently swing and smash its hammer at anything it feels like bothering. Do not get in the way!
column14:

column15:

column16:
O Touro Grande talvez fosse melhor descrito como um "grande valentão"...

Não tem como negociar com ele, e persistirá em balançar e acertar seu martelo em tudo que estiver a fim de incomodar. Saia da frente!
